Package com.atakmap.map.layer.raster

Interface RasterDataAccess2

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GLQuadTileNode4, GLTilePatch2
    public interface RasterDataAccess2
    Provides access to the underlying raster data in the RasterLayer.

    The image-to-ground and ground-to-image functions provide conversion between pixel coordinates in the image and geodetic coordinates. This coordinate transformation is based on the projection of the imagery as well as the registration of the imagery on the map and should be considered an interpolative transformation. These functions are not sufficient for imagery with robust image-to-ground and ground-to-image functions. Data with robust functions should utilize the PrecisionRasterDataAccess subinterface.

    See Also:
    com.atakmap.map.layer.raster.PrecisionRasterDataAccess, com.atakmap.map.layer.raster.RasterLayer#getService(Class), com.atakmap.map.layer.raster.service.RasterDataAccessService
